            "anno_id": 1,
            "text": " This ratio is greater than 1 for large t (as soon as  $t > 2^{\\frac{n}{n-1}}(Isop(L))^{-1}$ ). Letting  $T$  be an appropriate affine transform, i.e.  $Te_n = t_0 e_n$ , and  $Te_i = e_i$  ( $i \\leq n-1$ ), where  $t_0$  is large  enough, one deduces that  $b_2(C) = b_2(TC) > 1$ , because  $\\frac{Isop(TL)}{Isop(TC)} = \\frac{Isop(L)}{Isop(TC)} > 1$ .  ",
