            "text": " d- The half-ball. Denote  $H_+ = \\{x_n \\ge 0\\}$  a closed half-space,  $B_2^n$  the (unit) Euclidean ball, andd- The half-ball. Denote  $H_+ = \\{x_n \\geq 0\\}$  a closed half-space,  $B_2^n$  the (unit) Euclidean ball, and   $M = H_+ \\cap B_2^n$  a half-ball. Then  $|M|_n = \\kappa_n/2$ ,  $|\\partial M|_{n-1} = \\frac{n\\kappa_n}{2} + \\kappa_{n-1}$ , and so  $\\text{Isop}(M) = 1 + \\frac{2\\kappa_{n-1}}{n\\kappa_n}$ . The unique facet of  $M$  is  $F \\approx B_2^{n-1}$ , and so  $\\text{Isop}(F) = 1$ . Hence  $\\frac{\\text{Isop}(F)}{\\text{Isop}(M)} < 1$ .",
