            "text": " If  $\\Delta_n = Conv(0, e_1, ..., e_n)$ , then  $|\\Delta_n| = \\frac{1}{n!}$ , and  $|\\partial \\Delta_n| = \\frac{n}{(n-1)!} + \\frac{\\sqrt{n}}{(n-1)!}$ , hence  $\\text{Isop}(\\Delta_n) = n+\\sqrt{n}$ . There are two kinds of facets : one is  $\\Delta_{n-1}$ , the other one is  $T_{n-1}$ . Their isoperimetric ratios are respectively  $\\text{Isop}(T_{n-1}) = \\sqrt{n(n-1)}$  and  $\\text{Isop}(\\Delta_{n-1}) = n-1+\\sqrt{n-1} > \\text{Isop}(T_{n-1})$ . Therefore :",
